hpicfVsfVCMIB.name: hpicfVsfVCMIB
hpicfVsfVCMIB.contactinfo: Hewlett Packard Company 8000 Foothills Blvd. Roseville, CA 95747
hpicfVsfVCMIB.description: This MIB module describes the objects that are used to manage VSF Virtual Chassis feature.

hpicfVsfVCDomainId.name: hpicfVsfVCDomainId
hpicfVsfVCDomainId.description: The VSF virtual chassis domain ID uniquely identifies the VSF virtual chassis; all members of the virtual chassis have the same virtual chassis domain ID. The VSF virtual chassis domain ID is valid only when hpicfVsfVCSwitchAdminStatus is set to true (1). This value is set by the first elected commander of the VSF virtual chassis.

hpicfVsfVCOperStatus.name: hpicfVsfVCOperStatus
hpicfVsfVCOperStatus.description: This is the current operational status of the VSF virtual chassis.

hpicfVsfVCAdminStatus.name: hpicfVsfVCAdminStatus
hpicfVsfVCAdminStatus.description: The administrative status of the VSF virtual chassis. When set to enable (1), this object enables VSF on the switch and on the discovered members. Setting this to disable (2) disables VSF only on the standalone switch. Enabling or disabling VSF triggers a reboot of the VSF switch.

hpicfVsfVCTopology.name: hpicfVsfVCTopology
hpicfVsfVCTopology.description: This object describes the physical topology of the VSF virtual chassis.

hpicfVsfVCTrapEnable.name: hpicfVsfVCTrapEnable
hpicfVsfVCTrapEnable.description: This object controls the ability of the VSF virtual chassis to send traps.

hpicfVsfVCOobmMADEnable.name: hpicfVsfVCOobmMADEnable
hpicfVsfVCOobmMADEnable.description: This object enables the VSF OOBM MAD (Multi-Active Detection) feature.

hpicfVsfLldpMADEnable.name: hpicfVsfLldpMADEnable
hpicfVsfLldpMADEnable.description: This object enables the VSF LLDP MAD (Multi-Active Detection) feature.

hpicfVsfVCLldpMADDeviceIpType.name: hpicfVsfVCLldpMADDeviceIpType
hpicfVsfVCLldpMADDeviceIpType.description: This object provides the address type of the VSF LLDP MAD (Multi-Active Detection)device.

hpicfVsfVCLldpMADDeviceIpAddr.name: hpicfVsfVCLldpMADDeviceIpAddr
hpicfVsfVCLldpMADDeviceIpAddr.description: This object provides the IPv4/IPv6 address of the VSF LLDP MAD (Multi-Active Detection) device.

hpicfVsfVCLldpMADSnmpVersion.name: hpicfVsfVCLldpMADSnmpVersion
hpicfVsfVCLldpMADSnmpVersion.description: This object provides the VSF LLDP MAD (Multi-Active Detection) SNMP version.

hpicfVsfVCLldpMADSnmpCommunity.name: hpicfVsfVCLldpMADSnmpCommunity
hpicfVsfVCLldpMADSnmpCommunity.description: This object provides the VSF LLDP MAD (Multi-Active Detection) SNMP community-string.

hpicfVsfMADVlan.name: hpicfVsfMADVlan
hpicfVsfMADVlan.description: This object configures the VLAN as a Multi-Active Detection (MAD) VLAN. The MAD VLAN will be used to send and receive discovery packets to detect virtual chassis fragments in case of a split. The default value (0) of the object indicates that no MAD VLAN is currently configured.

hpicfVsfMADVlanConnectivity.name: hpicfVsfMADVlanConnectivity
hpicfVsfMADVlanConnectivity.description: This object indicates the connectivity state of Multi- Active-Detection (MAD) VLAN. none (1) - When the MAD VLAN does not have any operational port in all member switches. full (2) - When the MAD VLAN has one up port in all member switches. partial (3) - When the MAD VLAN has some up ports but does not have an operational port in all member switches.

hpicfVsfVCPortSpeed.name: hpicfVsfVCPortSpeed
hpicfVsfVCPortSpeed.description: This object is used to set the speed of all VSF ports. If this object is not set, it is automatically set to the maximum speed of the first link port added to the VSF. The value none(0) indicates that no VSF links have been added so the speed is unknown.

hpicfVsfVCLldpMADReadinessStatus.name: hpicfVsfVCLldpMADReadinessStatus
hpicfVsfVCLldpMADReadinessStatus.description: This object indicates the readiness state of VSF LLDP MAD (Multi-Active Detection).

hpicfVsfVCLldpMADDeviceMAC.name: hpicfVsfVCLldpMADDeviceMAC
hpicfVsfVCLldpMADDeviceMAC.description: This object indicates the MAC address of the VSF LLDP MAD (Multi-Active Detection) helper-device.

hpicfVsfVCLldpMADVlanId.name: hpicfVsfVCLldpMADVlanId
hpicfVsfVCLldpMADVlanId.description: This object indicates the VLAN-ID of the domain on which the VSF LLDP MAD (Multi-Active Detection) helper-device resides.

hpicfVsfVCLldpMADTrunkIfIndex.name: hpicfVsfVCLldpMADTrunkIfIndex
hpicfVsfVCLldpMADTrunkIfIndex.description: This object indicates the trunk ifIndex of the interface on the VSF device that is connected to the VSF LLDP MAD (Multi-Active Detection) helper-device.

hpicfVsfVCLldpMADProbePortSet.name: hpicfVsfVCLldpMADProbePortSet
hpicfVsfVCLldpMADProbePortSet.description: This object indicates the list of physical ports on the VSF LLDP MAD (Multi-Active Detection) helper-device that will be probed for operational status during MAD probe.

hpicfVsfVCLldpMADConnectivity.name: hpicfVsfVCLldpMADConnectivity
hpicfVsfVCLldpMADConnectivity.description: This object indicates the reachability state of the VSF LLDP MAD (Multi-Active Detection) helper-device. none (1) - When there is no connectivity to the LLDP MAD helper-device. full (2) - When the LAG has at least one physical port in the enabled state on every VSF member switch. partial (3) - When the LAG does not have at least one enabled VSF physical port on every VSF member switch.

hpicfVsfVCLldpMADSplitStatus.name: hpicfVsfVCLldpMADSplitStatus
hpicfVsfVCLldpMADSplitStatus.description: This object indicates the VSF LLDP MAD (Multi-Active Detection) split status.

hpicfVsfVCLldpMADProbeOriginator.name: hpicfVsfVCLldpMADProbeOriginator
hpicfVsfVCLldpMADProbeOriginator.description: This object indicates whether the VSF fragment is running the VSF LLDP MAD (Multi-Active Detection) probe or not.

hpicfVsfVCLldpMADProbeRequestsSent.name: hpicfVsfVCLldpMADProbeRequestsSent
hpicfVsfVCLldpMADProbeRequestsSent.description: This is the number of SNMP queries sent to the VSF LLDP MAD (Multi-Active Detection) helper-device.

hpicfVsfVCLldpMADProbeResponseRcvd.name: hpicfVsfVCLldpMADProbeResponseRcvd
hpicfVsfVCLldpMADProbeResponseRcvd.description: This is the number of SNMP responses received from the VSF LLDP MAD (Multi-Active Detection) helper-device.

hpicfVsfVCLldpMADActiveFragment.name: hpicfVsfVCLldpMADActiveFragment
hpicfVsfVCLldpMADActiveFragment.description: This object specifies whether this VSF fragment is the active or an inactive fragment.

hpicfVsfVCMemberTable.name: hpicfVsfVCMemberTable
hpicfVsfVCMemberTable.description: This table contains information about the VSF virtual chassis members.

hpicfVsfVCMemberEntry.name: hpicfVsfVCMemberEntry
hpicfVsfVCMemberEntry.description: A row in the VSF virtual chassis member table.

hpicfVsfVCMemberId.name: hpicfVsfVCMemberId
hpicfVsfVCMemberId.description: This object describes the VSF virtual chassis member ID.

hpicfVsfVCMemberProductId.name: hpicfVsfVCMemberProductId
hpicfVsfVCMemberProductId.description: This object describes the type of VSF member-switch.

hpicfVsfVCMemberMacAddr.name: hpicfVsfVCMemberMacAddr
hpicfVsfVCMemberMacAddr.description: This object specifies the VSF member-switch MAC address.

hpicfVsfVCMemberShutdown.name: hpicfVsfVCMemberShutdown
hpicfVsfVCMemberShutdown.description: When this object is set to true (1) for a specific active-member VSF virtual chassis switch, that switch will shut down. Setting the object to false (2) has no effect. This object cannot be set to true (1) if the specified member is an VSF commander. If the VSF member is in standby mode, a new standby switch is chosen. The VSF member shutdown is prevented if it will cause a virtual chassis split.

hpicfVsfVCMemberReboot.name: hpicfVsfVCMemberReboot
hpicfVsfVCMemberReboot.description: When set to true (1), this object will reboot the VSF member-switch. Setting the object to false (2) has no effect. Reboot is prevented if it will cause a virtual chassis split.

hpicfVsfVCMemberAdminPriority.name: hpicfVsfVCMemberAdminPriority
hpicfVsfVCMemberAdminPriority.description: This object allows the user to set the priority of a switch when VSF is enabled on it.

hpicfVsfVCMemberEntryStatus.name: hpicfVsfVCMemberEntryStatus
hpicfVsfVCMemberEntryStatus.description: This object indicates the row status of an VSF virtual chassis-member entry. If the VSF member ID corresponds to an VSF commander, the row cannot be destroyed. For active switches, if hpicfVsfVCMemberReboot is set to true (1), and the row status is set to destroy (6), the switch comes up with a default configuration and acquires a new hpicfVsfVCMemberId.

hpicfVsfVCMemberEntPhysicalIndex.name: hpicfVsfVCMemberEntPhysicalIndex
hpicfVsfVCMemberEntPhysicalIndex.description: This object specifies the entPhysicalTable (rfc2737) index of the VSF member.

hpicfVsfVCMemberState.name: hpicfVsfVCMemberState
hpicfVsfVCMemberState.description: This object gives the status of the member-switch in the VSF virtual chassis. unusedId (0) - The member ID does not exist. missing (1) - An VSF virtual chassis member-switch is marked as missing when it becomes non-responsive. A lack of response from the switch means that either the virtual chassis link or the virtual chassis member has crashed. Note that it is possible to remove a missing member from the virtual chassis. Once removed, the missing member's configuration will be deleted from the virtual chassis configuration file. provision (2) - A member-switch that is not physically present but whose configuration is provisioned . commander (3) - The member-switch which is the commander of the VSF virtual chassis. standby (4) - The member-switch which is the standby of the VSF virtual chassis. member (5) - The member-switch that is a part of the VSF virtual chassis. shutdown (6) - The member-switch is in the shut down state. booting (7) - The member-switch is booting. communicationFailure (8)- The member-switch cannot be reached. incompatibleOS (9) - The member-switch is running with a different Operating System. unknownState (10) - The state of the member-switch cannot be determined. standbyBooting (11)- The standby switch is currently booting up. When the switch finishes booting, its state will change to standby (4).

hpicfVsfVCMemberProductName.name: hpicfVsfVCMemberProductName
hpicfVsfVCMemberProductName.description: The product name of the VSF member-switch.

hpicfVsfVCMemberUpTime.name: hpicfVsfVCMemberUpTime
hpicfVsfVCMemberUpTime.description: This object provides the uptime of the VSF member-switch. This is different from the VSF chassis uptime.

hpicfVsfVCMemberSysOid.name: hpicfVsfVCMemberSysOid
hpicfVsfVCMemberSysOid.description: This object provides the sysObjectId of the VSF member-switch.

hpicfVsfVCMemberIdForTrap.name: hpicfVsfVCMemberIdForTrap
hpicfVsfVCMemberIdForTrap.description: The member ID used in trap notifications. This is the same value as hpicfVsfVCMemberId.

hpicfVsfVCMemberSerialNum.name: hpicfVsfVCMemberSerialNum
hpicfVsfVCMemberSerialNum.description: This object specifies the serial number of the VSF member-switch.

hpicfVsfVCMemberBootRomVersion.name: hpicfVsfVCMemberBootRomVersion
hpicfVsfVCMemberBootRomVersion.description: This object specifies the boot-ROM version of the VSF member-switch.

hpicfVsfVCMemberOsVersion.name: hpicfVsfVCMemberOsVersion
hpicfVsfVCMemberOsVersion.description: This object specifies the operating system version of the VSF member-switch.

hpicfVsfVCMemberBootImage.name: hpicfVsfVCMemberBootImage
hpicfVsfVCMemberBootImage.description: This object specifies the boot image of the VSF member-switch.

hpicfVsfVCMemberRenumber.name: hpicfVsfVCMemberRenumber
hpicfVsfVCMemberRenumber.description: This object specifies the new member ID to be assigned to this VSF virtual chassis member-switch.

hpicfVsfVCMemberCpuUtil.name: hpicfVsfVCMemberCpuUtil
hpicfVsfVCMemberCpuUtil.description: This object provides the percentage of CPU utilization of the VSF member-switch.

hpicfVsfVCMemberTotalMemory.name: hpicfVsfVCMemberTotalMemory
hpicfVsfVCMemberTotalMemory.description: This object provides the total memory usage in bytes of the VSF member-switch.

hpicfVsfVCMemberFreeMemory.name: hpicfVsfVCMemberFreeMemory
hpicfVsfVCMemberFreeMemory.description: This object provides the free memory available, in bytes, on the VSF member-switch.

hpicfVsfVCLinkTable.name: hpicfVsfVCLinkTable
hpicfVsfVCLinkTable.description: This table contains information about the VSF links. An VSF link is a logical interface for the connection between VSF member devices. To use an VSF link, you must bind at least one physical port to it. These ports are called 'VSF physical ports' or 'VSF Ports'. The physical ports assigned to an VSF link automatically form an aggregate VSF link. An VSF link goes down only if all of its members' physical ports are down.

hpicfVsfVCLinkEntry.name: hpicfVsfVCLinkEntry
hpicfVsfVCLinkEntry.description: A row in the VSF link table.

hpicfVsfVCLinkMemberId.name: hpicfVsfVCLinkMemberId
hpicfVsfVCLinkMemberId.description: This object is the member ID of the VSF virtual chassis to which this VSF link belongs.

hpicfVsfVCLinkId.name: hpicfVsfVCLinkId
hpicfVsfVCLinkId.description: This object indicates the link ID for this VSF entry.

hpicfVsfVCLinkName.name: hpicfVsfVCLinkName
hpicfVsfVCLinkName.description: This object indicates the VSF link name. The maximum allowed link name is 32 characters.

hpicfVsfVCLinkOperStatus.name: hpicfVsfVCLinkOperStatus
hpicfVsfVCLinkOperStatus.description: This object indicates the VSF link state.

hpicfVsfVCPeerMemberId.name: hpicfVsfVCPeerMemberId
hpicfVsfVCPeerMemberId.description: This object indicates the peer-member ID to which the VSF link is connected.

hpicfVsfVCPeerLinkId.name: hpicfVsfVCPeerLinkId
hpicfVsfVCPeerLinkId.description: This object indicates the VSF link ID of the peer-member to which this VSF link is connected.

hpicfVsfVCLinkPortList.name: hpicfVsfVCLinkPortList
hpicfVsfVCLinkPortList.description: This object indicates the list of physical ports belonging to this VSF link.

hpicfVsfVCLinkEntryStatus.name: hpicfVsfVCLinkEntryStatus
hpicfVsfVCLinkEntryStatus.description: This object indicates the row status of an VSF virtual chassis link entry.

hpicfVsfVCLinkIdForTrap.name: hpicfVsfVCLinkIdForTrap
hpicfVsfVCLinkIdForTrap.description: This object indicates the VSF virtual chassis link ID used in trap notifications. This is the same value as hpicfVsfVCLinkId.

hpicfVsfVCLinkPortStartState.name: hpicfVsfVCLinkPortStartState
hpicfVsfVCLinkPortStartState.description: This object indicates whether ports should be enabled while creating the VSF virtual chassis link.

hpicfVsfVCPortTable.name: hpicfVsfVCPortTable
hpicfVsfVCPortTable.description: This table contains information about the VSF virtual chassis physical ports.

hpicfVsfVCPortEntry.name: hpicfVsfVCPortEntry
hpicfVsfVCPortEntry.description: A row in the VSF port table.

hpicfVsfVCPortOperStatus.name: hpicfVsfVCPortOperStatus
hpicfVsfVCPortOperStatus.description: This object provides the VSF virtual chassis physical port state.

hpicfVsfVCPortOperStatusErrorStr.name: hpicfVsfVCPortOperStatusErrorStr
hpicfVsfVCPortOperStatusErrorStr.description: This object provides an error message if hpicfVsfVCPortOperStatus returns the value error (3).

hpicfVsfVCCommanderChange.name: hpicfVsfVCCommanderChange
hpicfVsfVCCommanderChange.description: This notification is generated when a new VSF commander first comes up. The notification is also sent when a failover happens, and the VSF standby becomes an VSF commander or when the VSF commander is down.

hpicfVsfVCMemberChange.name: hpicfVsfVCMemberChange
hpicfVsfVCMemberChange.description: This notification is generated when a new member joins the VSF virtual chassis or when a member switch is moved from the loose-provisioned state to the strict-provisioned state.

hpicfVsfVCMemberStatusChange.name: hpicfVsfVCMemberStatusChange
hpicfVsfVCMemberStatusChange.description: This notification is generated when an VSF member becomes active or inactive.

hpicfVsfVCConfigScalarGroup.name: hpicfVsfVCConfigScalarGroup
hpicfVsfVCConfigScalarGroup.description: A collection of VSF virtual chassis scalar objects.

hpicfVsfVCMemberTableGroup.name: hpicfVsfVCMemberTableGroup
hpicfVsfVCMemberTableGroup.description: A collection of VSF virtual chassis member table objects.

hpicfVsfVCLinkTableGroup.name: hpicfVsfVCLinkTableGroup
hpicfVsfVCLinkTableGroup.description: A collection of VSF virtual chassis link table objects.

hpicfVsfVCNotificationsGroup.name: hpicfVsfVCNotificationsGroup
hpicfVsfVCNotificationsGroup.description: A collection of VSF virtual chassis notifications objects.

hpicfVsfVCStatusScalarGroup.name: hpicfVsfVCStatusScalarGroup
hpicfVsfVCStatusScalarGroup.description: A collection of VSF virtual chassis notifications objects.

hpicfVsfVCPortTableGroup.name: hpicfVsfVCPortTableGroup
hpicfVsfVCPortTableGroup.description: A collection of VSF virtual chassis physical port objects.

hpicfVsfVCConfigScalarGroup1.name: hpicfVsfVCConfigScalarGroup1
hpicfVsfVCConfigScalarGroup1.description: A collection of VSF virtual chassis scalar objects.

hpicfVsfVCMibCompliance.name: hpicfVsfVCMibCompliance
hpicfVsfVCMibCompliance.description: The compliance statement for devices implementing the HP VSF VC Mib.

hpicfVsfVCMibCompliance1.name: hpicfVsfVCMibCompliance1
hpicfVsfVCMibCompliance1.description: The compliance statement for devices implementing the HP VSF VC Mib.
